24/06/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- As expected, the government approved on Monday (23 June) a defence ministry plan reducing the length of mandatory military service by three months. The plan is based on an assessment that concluded risks to stability are lower both at home and abroad. The change could help save as much as $175m annually.
In other news, a parliamentary delegation arrived in Washington on Tuesday to meet with representatives of the National Security Council, the commerce, defence and treasury departments, the IMF and the World Bank. Talks will focus on opportunities for development of economic and investment ties. (Anadolu Agency - 24/06/03; Anadolu Agency, AFP - 23/06/03)
